  "text": "Loss of the ability to balance is associated with a higher risk of falling and subsequent injury, which in turn can lead to loss of independence, illness, and premature mortality [CITATION_1] . BC activities have been shown to be a critical part of an effective falls prevention programme [CITATION_2] . One meta-analysis concluded that up to 42 % of falls could be prevented by a well-designed exercise programme that included BC activities [CITATION_3] .",
